data.content:
The best approach for your file system statics is to adopt the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package â€” it's battle-tested and covers `File.*`, `Directory.*`, and `Path.*` with a mock-friendly API. No need to write custom wrappers.

Looking at your `ReportGenerator`, it actually has **four** categories of untestable statics:

| Static | Recommended Abstraction |
|---|---|
| `File.WriteAllText`, `Directory.Exists/CreateDirectory` | **`System.IO.Abstractions`** (NuGet) |
| `DateTime.UtcNow` | **`TimeProvider`** (built-in on .NET 10) |
| `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable`, `Environment.MachineName` | Custom **`IEnvironmentProvider`** wrapper |
| `Console.WriteLine` | Custom **`IConsole`** wrapper (or just remove from this class) |

Here's how to adopt each:

---

### 1. File System â€” `System.IO.Abstractions`

Install in your project:
```
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
```

Install the test helpers in your test project:
```
dotnet add <TestProject> package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

Inject `IFileSystem` and use `fileSystem.File.*`, `fileSystem.Directory.*`, `fileSystem.Path.*`:

```csharp
public class ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem, ...)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, ...);
        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);
        return reportPath;
    }
}
```

Register in DI:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

Test with `MockFileSystem`:
```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
mockFs.AddDirectory("/tmp/reports");
var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs, ...);

generator.GenerateReport("Sales");

Assert.True(mockFs.File.Exists(
    mockFs.AllFiles.Single(f => f.Contains("Sales"))));
```

---

### 2. Time â€” built-in `TimeProvider`

Since you're on .NET 10, no NuGet needed. Register and inject:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton(TimeProvider.System);
```

```csharp
public class ReportGenerator(..., TimeProvider timeProvider)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        var timestamp = timeProvider.GetUtcNow().ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss");
        // ...
    }
}
```

Test with `FakeTimeProvider` (from `Microsoft.Extensions.TimeProvider.Testing`):
```csharp
var fakeTime = new FakeTimeProvider(
    new DateTimeOffset(2026, 1, 15, 12, 0, 0, TimeSpan.Zero));
var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs, fakeTime, ...);
// Now timestamps are deterministic in tests
```

---

### 3. Environment â€” custom `IEnvironmentProvider`

Only wrap the two methods you actually use:

```csharp
public interface IEnvironmentProvider
{
    string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable);
    string MachineName { get; }
}

public sealed class EnvironmentProvider : IEnvironmentProvider
{
    public string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable)
        => Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(variable);

    public string MachineName => Environment.MachineName;
}
```

Register: `builder.Services.AddSingleton<IEnvironmentProvider, EnvironmentProvider>();`

---

### Refactored `ReportGenerator`

Putting it all together:

```csharp
public class ReportGenerator(
    IFileSystem fileSystem,
    TimeProvider timeProvider,
    IEnvironmentProvider environment)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        var timestamp = timeProvider.GetUtcNow().ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss");
        var outputDir = environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("REPORT_OUTPUT_DIR") ?? "/tmp/reports";

        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, $"{reportName}_{timestamp}.txt");
        var content = $"Report: {reportName}\nGenerated: {timeProvider.GetUtcNow():O}\nMachine: {environment.MachineName}";

        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);
        return reportPath;
    }
}
```

